Content:
The 2009 Autosport 1000km of Silverstone was the fifth and final round of the 2009 Le Mans Series season. It took place at the Silverstone Circuit, England, on 13 September 2009. The race was won from pole position by Olivier Panis and Nicolas Lapierre for Team Oreca, while the third place finishing Aston Martin of Jan Charouz, Tom Enge and Stefan Mcke won the LMP1 championship. Speedy Racing Team Sebah won their first race in the LMP2 category while the ASM Team failed to finish but were able to win their championship. First-time LMS entrant Gigawave Motorsport led the GT1 category while JMW Motorsport won in GT2. Team Felbermayr-Proton secured the GT2 class championship by finishing in seventh in their class. Pole position winners in each class are marked in bold.[1] Class winners in bold. Cars failing to complete 70% of winner's distance marked as Not Classified (NC).[2] 
